<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="475" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,150,393]" pageId="8" pageNumber="475">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,151,177]" pageId="8" pageNumber="475">Remarks.</emphasis>
The studied specimen (MNHN-IM-2013-67052) is damaged, lacking the head valve. It has 14–17 pores of aesthetes in each granule, 14 gills arranged from valve VI to near the anus, a radula 
<quantity box="[1200,1286,186,213]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.8" pageId="8" pageNumber="475" unit="mm" value="5.8">5.8 mm</quantity>
long with 35 transverse rows of mature teeth. The species belongs to the group of 
<emphasis box="[928,944,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="475">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[958,1205,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="475">
rissoi-L. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sirenko" authorityYear="1998" box="[1060,1205,223,248]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="8" pageNumber="475" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="vietnamensis">vietnamensis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and differs from the other species of this group by having 14–17 aesthete pores in the granules of the central areas (vs. 7–9 pores in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Nierstrasz" baseAuthorityYear="1905" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="8" pageNumber="475" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="rissoi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="475">L. rissoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 18–21 pores in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sirenko" authorityYear="1998" box="[405,580,295,320]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="8" pageNumber="475" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="vietnamensis">
<emphasis box="[405,580,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="475">L. vietnamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Moreover, the central tooth of the radula of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saito" authorityYear="2001" box="[1103,1263,295,321]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="8" pageNumber="475" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="longispinus">
<emphasis box="[1103,1263,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="475">L. longispinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows a longitudinal rib (vs. no longitudinal rib in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Nierstrasz" baseAuthorityYear="1905" box="[568,660,331,356]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="8" pageNumber="475" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="rissoi">
<emphasis box="[568,660,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="475">L. rissoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the granules in the central areas are separated from each other in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saito" authorityYear="2001" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="8" pageNumber="475" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="longispinus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="475">L. longispinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(vs. granules overlapping each other in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sirenko" authorityYear="1998" box="[730,904,367,392]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="8" pageNumber="475" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="vietnamensis">
<emphasis box="[730,904,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="475">L. vietnamensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
